cooking_instructions: Place one red mushroom, one brown mushroom, and a bowl together to craft a mushroom stew. No cooking required!
Mix all ingredients into a smooth batter, pour into a bundt pan, and bake at 350°F (175°C) for 25–30 minutes until golden. Let cool before serving.
Sauté garlic in olive oil, add seafood, cook for a few minutes. Add tomatoes and rice, then pour in broth with saffron. Simmer until rice is tender and seafood is cooked.
Boil rice, grill sausages, sauté vegetables with curry powder and water until thick. Serve over rice with sausages on top.

recipe_name: Elven Lembas Bread (Lord of the Rings games)
cooking_instructions: Mix all ingredients to form dough. Flatten and bake at 375°F (190°C) for 20 minutes until golden. Cut into squares.
Cook ground beef with chopped onions and chili powder, add tomato sauce and simmer. Serve over grilled hot dogs in buns.

recipe_name: Yeto's Soup (The Legend of Zelda: Twilight Princess)
cooking_instructions: Boil chopped pumpkin in milk until soft. Add reekfish and cook until flaky. Stir in goat cheese and salt to taste. Simmer before serving.
Boil spaghetti. Cook beef with onions and garlic. Add tomato sauce, salt, and pepper. Simmer and serve over pasta.
Bread pork cutlets and fry until golden. Make curry with roux and serve over rice. Top with cutlets.
Shred vegetables. Mix vinegar, sugar, and salt to make dressing. Toss vegetables and refrigerate for 1 hour before serving.
